Sentencas: Novel composite oxide ion conductors were developed based on a fluorite-type Ce0.8Y0.2O1.9 (CYO) and a perovsldte-type BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O2.9 (BZCYO) synthesized by the carbonate co-precipitation route at 700 degrees C and the sol-gel process at 1000 C, respectively.
Titulo: CYO-BZCYO composites with enhanced proton conductivity: Candidate electrolytes for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
